# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .dockerignore — keep the Docker build context lean.
#
# Why this file exists:
#   The deploy pipeline copies the whole repo into the build image
#   (`COPY . /app`). Without this file the frontend `node_modules`
#   (≈ 650 MB!) was being sent over, pushing the image manifest past
#   Artifact Registry's allowed size and failing with
#   `manifest invalid: Request contains an invalid argument.`
#
#   The backend image only needs:
#     - /app/backend/**  (Python + requirements.txt)
#     - /app/frontend/.env  (read by the build step for URL rewriting)
#     - top-level configs (entrypoint.sh, nginx.conf, package.json)
#
#   The frontend bundle is built separately by the EAS update step,
#   so node_modules / native projects must NOT travel with the
#   backend image.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Frontend deps & build artifacts (the big offender) ────────────
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/.expo/
frontend/.expo-shared/
frontend/dist/
frontend/web-build/
frontend/android/
frontend/ios/
frontend/.metro-cache/
frontend/.cache/

# ── Native SDK / Gradle / Xcode caches ────────────────────────────
android-sdk/
**/.gradle/
**/build/
**/DerivedData/

# ── Common dev clutter ────────────────────────────────────────────
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/node_modules/
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
*.log
*.swp
*.tmp

# ── Source control & editor ───────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore
.vscode/
.idea/
.emergent/

# ── Local-only directories ────────────────────────────────────────
test_reports/
tests/
memory/test_credentials.md

# ── Archive / binary files that should never be in a build ────────
**/*.zip
**/*.tar
**/*.tar.gz
**/*.tgz
**/*.7z
**/*.rar
**/*.apk
**/*.aab
**/*.ipa
**/*.dmg
**/*.deb
**/*.pack
**/*.dylib

# ── Keep these explicitly (just in case) ──────────────────────────
# (.dockerignore supports negation with !path; leaving the .env files
#  in the context because the backend build sed-rewrites them.)
!backend/.env
!frontend/.env
